Cloakfox: invoke one-shot pref migration at BrowserGlue startup.

On cpp-first build upgrades, existing profiles may have roverfox.s.*
prefs (from the pre-cpp-first extension era) that need to be mirrored
into cloakfox.s.* so the user's existing per-container seeds survive.
CloakfoxPrefMigration.sys.mjs runs once, then marks
cloakfox.migration.v1.done=true.

Hooked into _beforeUIStartup so it runs before any window is
constructed — so the cpp-first JSWindowActors that fire on
DOMDocElementInserted see the migrated values immediately.

--- a/browser/components/BrowserGlue.sys.mjs
+++ b/browser/components/BrowserGlue.sys.mjs
@@ -382,6 +382,18 @@

   _beforeUIStartup: function BG__beforeUIStartup() {
+    // Cloakfox: migrate legacy roverfox.s.* prefs (extension era) to
+    // cloakfox.s.* (cpp-first namespace). Idempotent; marks done on
+    // first run. See additions/browser/components/cloakfox/
+    // CloakfoxPrefMigration.sys.mjs.
+    try {
+      const { runCloakfoxPrefMigration } = ChromeUtils.importESModule(
+        "resource:///modules/CloakfoxPrefMigration.sys.mjs"
+      );
+      runCloakfoxPrefMigration();
+    } catch (_e) {
+      // Migration module missing on non-Cloakfox builds — ignore.
+    }
     lazy.SessionStartup.init();

     // check if we're in safe mode
